'Why SunflowerVN';//content$_['sv_content_scope']='<ul class="BossListContent"><li>SmartBiz’s SMART Implementation Methodology:<ul><li><b>S</b>pecifications or customer requirements</li><li><b>M</b>anagement of Change</li><li><b>A</b>lternatives consideration</li><li><b>R</b>ecognition of Benefits</li><li><b>T</b>otal Cost of Ownership</li></ul><li>Features of SmartBiz’s SMART Implementation<ul><li>SmartBiz’s methodologies were consolidated by industry experiences, researches, and specific preferences of Vietnam market.</li><li>Through its expertise and leadership in integration SmartBiz’s Smart Implementation ensures all components of a chosen ERP package are delivered         on schedule and at the mutually agreed price.</li><li>SmartBiz offers on-site expertise as well as call-center support.</li><li>Services methodology is executed by a multi-disciplined and experienced project team.</li></ul></li></ul>';$_['sv_content_implementation']='<ul class="BossListContent"><li>ERP-Implemetation is divided into 3 main implementation phases (with each phase having numerous tasks):<ul><li>Pre-Implementation Phase</li><li>Implementation Phase</li><li>Post-Implementation Phase</li></ul></li><li>ERP-Implemetation is step by step by step... That’s our approach to implementation. No Big Bang. No throwing out legacy systems that are working well, but just a smooth transition into ERP-Implemetation.</li> <li>ERP-Customization is to be modified accordingly with client requirements and prevailing circumstances of the client business environment.</li></ul>';$_['sv_content_requirement']='';$_['sv_content_network']='';$_['sv_content_migration']='';$_['sv_content_post_implementation']='<ul class="BossListContent"><li>Review & Finalize - Business Requirements</li> <li>Review & Finalize - License and Services Agreement</li> <li>Review & Finalize - Project Scope, Plan, Milestones and Budget</li> <li>Review & Finalize - Change Control Procedures</li> <li>Review & Finalize - Data Migration Plan</li> </ul>';//$_['sv_approach_content'] = '<ul class="BossListContent"><li>Customer focus<ul><li>The agile approach puts a strong focus on the customer, often having a customer representative in each agile team.</li></ul></li><li>Quality<ul><li>The agile approach requires delivering working software on a frequent basis. That software must be of a high quality–technical excellence and good design.</li></ul></li><li>Change is good<ul><li>Work is broken up into smaller chunks with less of a rigid plan. These iterations typically last from one to four weeks. Change is embraced, allowing the development process to be more "agile".</li></ul></li><li>Teamwork</li></ul>';$_['sv_SOA_content'] = '<ul class="BossListContent"><li>Enterprise Service Bus (ESB) allows different applications (regardless JMS, Web Services, JDBC, HTTP, and more)to communicate with each other by acting as a transit system for carrying data between applications within your enterprise or across the Internet, including:    <ul>    <li> Service creation and hosting — expose and host reusable services</li>    <li> Service mediation — shield services from message formats and protocols, separate business logic from messaging, and enable location-independent service calls</li>    <li> Message routing — route, filter, aggregate, and re-sequence messages based on content and rules</li>    <li> Data transformation — exchange data across varying formats and transport protocols</li>    </ul>    </li></ul>';$_['sv_networking_content'] = '<ul class="BossListContent"><li>Collecting client’s technical and business requirements.</li><li>Studying client’s existing network system.</li><li>Providing general design.</li><li>Providing detailed design, including: <ul><li>Description of data flow.</li><li>Network services.</li><li>Logic design.</li><li>Physical topology.</li><li>Routing system</li><li>Addressing.</li></ul></li><li>Providing client with general and detailed designs.    </li><li>Our commitment:<ul><li>Stable network infrastructure complying with international standards.</li><li>State-of-the-art technology.</li><li>Minimized cost and time by standard design and avoidance of unneccessary devices caused by wrong design.</li></ul></li></ul>';$_['sv_architecture_content'] = 'UC Technical Architecture';$_['sv_workflow_content'] = 'UC Stock Out Workflow';$_['sv_master_plan_content'] = 'The String provides a blueprint of the future information technology for customers. It utilizes an integrated approach for the use of technology to meet the business requirements.<br /><br /><ol><li>1.	An effective organizational structure is essential for market leadership and management of a rapidly evolving technological environment.</li><li>2.	The efficiency and effectiveness of business support services requires compatibility and integration between technology systems and applications.</li><li>3.	The successful use of technology in daily tasks requires technology enhanced classrooms and instructional support services.</li><li>4.	Adequate financial structures are essential for the implementation of new technologies and the maintenance of existing technologies.</li><li>5.	Training of managers and staff is essential to take advantage of technology investments</li><li>6.	Business operations require a current, reliable and secure computing and network environment and responsive support systems.</li></ol><br /><br /><b>Components</b><br /><br /><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" style="border:solid 1px #333333"><tr style="border:solid 1px #333333">	<td style="border-bottom:solid 1px #333333;" height="20px" bgcolor="#999999" align="center" colspan="2">Hardware</td></tr><tr>	<td height="20px" style="padding-left:10px;border-bottom:solid 1px #333333;border-right:solid 1px #333333;" width="60%" align="left">		Network Infrastructure </td>	<td width="40%" style="padd